description:
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for an enthusiastic Communications and Marketing Assistant who can help deliver a range of targeted communications, ensuring our channels are a source of timely, accurate and relevant information for our audiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work primarily in the Internal Communications and Engagement team, but also provide support to the wider team including our Marketing and Events team and Media and Campaigns team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll provide support to the Internal Communications and Engagement Officers to collate and schedule content for our internal channels including the intranet and on-line collaboration tools such as Yammer, support with events (currently these are virtual events), and provide support for internal campaigns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be comfortable using technology such as Office 365 including Sharepoint, Teams and Yammer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll also work with our Creative Designers to develop content including graphics, video, audio, podcasts for internal and external projects, campaigns and initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll have excellent communication, administrative and organisational skills, enjoy creative, challenging work and be able to progress multiple tasks in a busy environment so good time management skills are a must.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A positive outlook and attitude are essential as well as being keen to try out new ideas. As the team is currently working remotely, we&#39;re looking for someone who is flexible and enthusiastic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal conversation about the post please contact Sharron Hodson, Internal Communications and Engagement Manager - 07776 680618 / sharron.hodson@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
